The author, who ran for president, has signed an executive order directing the Department of Justice to oversee a declassification review of documents related to the FBI's investigations into the September 11th attacks. The order requires the Attorney General to release the declassified documents publicly over the next six months. The author emphasizes the enduring pain of the families and loved ones of the victims, who have suffered personal devastation for the past 20 years. The author expresses solidarity with the 9/11 families and vows to engage respectfully with them as they work towards healing and finding a way forward.